args: This...isn't much, but it might help you.
Thank you! This should be enough to\ncover for my mistake. I don't know what\nI would've done without you.

Marvelous! I'm glad I could help!
I'll be waiting at home tonight with a big
pot of that homemade stew you love
so much, so don't be late!
Tch. What is this, a mouse's lunch money?\nCash sure don't flow like it used to. Guess\nit's about time I cut that broad loose.
Maybe I'll give that other chick the ol'\nsob story next! Geh heh heh!
Yeah, he does match the description.\nHey! You there!
What is it? Can't ya see I'm busy here?
We've got no beef with you, but we're\ngonna need you to come with us.
Miss Malora would like a word.\nAnd we don't like to keep her waiting.\nPREPARE YOURSELF!
Aaagh! What the heck?!\nI-I'm gettin' outta here!
Yo, that guy runnin' this wayâ€”\nI think he might be you-know-who!
It's the man that Malora is looking for!\nYou there! Stop!
Ain't gonna happen! You're my one-way\nticket to a steamy evenin' with Malora!
Eeek! Honestly, what is going on?!
L-looks like I managed to shake 'em.\nBut who's Malora? Some bimbo I tricked?\n...Ooh, wait a sec. Target sighted.

Perf. I'll dupe this little lady, have her
hide me somewhere safe, and then rob her
blind when she's turned the other cheek.
Geh heh heh.

You there! Miss! Please, a moment!
Kindness radiates from you in gossamer
waves, and I find myself in need of refuge
from a most dogged pursuant...
Goodness, you poor thing.\nYou know, when I look into your eyes,\nI see...
...a perfect match for the description that\nMalora gave me!
M-Malora again?! Wait, you can't mean...!
I'm going to catch you and hand you over\nto Malora!
You too?! But why the heck are YOU trying\nto capture me?!
Malora is offering a reward to whoever\ncatches you.

She offers the privilege of spending
Dragonyule with HER! Oh, to bask in her
radiance, laughing as we roast chestnuts
on an open fire... I! Must! Earn! It! HRAAH!
Where's that garbage man who makes\nladies cry?! I'm gonna find his sorry mug\nand offer his carcass up to Malora!
The heck is goin' on?! Everywhere I go,\npeople are all about this Malora woman...
Whatever the case, I can't stick around\nhere. I gotta get going while the going's\ngood!
*wheeze* Now...that I've come this far...\nI oughta be fine. Waiâ€”UWAAARGH!
What in the... Is this some kinda trap?!\nShoot! I'm caught in this net and I can't\nmove!
Oho ho! Oh-so-predictable, my dear\npilferer. Without anywhere to hide,\nI expected you to leave town.
The scoundrel who tricks and ensnares\nwomen is now the one caught in a trap.\nAren't life's little jokes hysterical?
This was YOUR doing?! Who are you?!\nAnd what the heck are you doing in that\nscrewy Saint Starfall costume?!
I'm not Saint Starfall. I am LADY Starfall,\ngreat and bewitching ally of love most\npure.
There's the garbage man!\nHe's with Malora!
ï¼‚Maloraï¼‚?! Wait, so YOU'RE the one who's\nbeen siccing all these people on me?!
Don't act so scandalized, my dear.\nI merely offered them a reward for their\nservices. Isn't that right, friends?

I mobilized my admirers and had them set
up a dragnet for you. My mother would
often use this method to track down her
bounties.

Charm and technique that inspires people
to action... These are the weapons I bring
to bear, courtesy of my dear mother.
Please, hold your applause.
Hey! You're one of the women I tricked!
I'm here on her behalf. And since we're\nhaving this little get-together, I called a\nfew OTHER faces you might recognize.
How could you toy with our pure hearts?!\nHere's that stew I promised youâ€”\nHave a taste! I INSIST!
This is payback for tricking me! TAKE THIS!
And now it's your turn, my lady.\nDo with him as you please.
Hey, hey, hey! You wouldn't hurt me\nlike these other gals, would you...?
H-hey, come on, can't you let this slide?\nWe swore our love to one another, didn't\nwe? Please! FORGIVE MEEE!
Every second I spend concerning myself\nwith this unsightly garbage is wasted.\nHe can rot in a cell for all I care.
Looks as though you've shaken off any\nlingering attachment to the man. All that\nremains is to retrieve what he stole.
Fess up. Where's my necklace?\nHurry and give it back.\nI'm tired of looking at you.
Huh? The necklace?\nI pawned it ages ago.
No! That was a keepsake my mother\nleft me!
Who did you sell it to?
If I tell you, will you let me go?
If you DON'T tell me, well... Who knows\nwhat grim fate might befall you? Oho ho!

Urgh... Look, there's this guy, Count
Delchi. Corrupt nobleman who buys up
stolen goods. Lives in a town called
Closeheide.
The count of Closeheide, hm? Very well.\nI'll go pay him a visit and get the necklace\nback.

I told you, didn't I? He who opens the door
to the realm of passion is beholden to his
charge until the bittersweet end. Requests
like this are no different. I'll handle it.
Still, cozying up to the Count will be\nno mean feat.
No matter how slippery the target,\nnone shall elude Lady Starfall!
Hmph. Sure, you might be able to outwit\nthe Count. But necklace or no, you'll\nnever escape the town alive.
And why is that? Is there something I\nshould know about this town of\nCloseheide?

Listen up, soldiers! This town is a
cornerstone of the Empire's defenses!
Arrest any and all suspicious persons on
sight!
(Say, doesn't the captain seem awfully\nfired up today?)
(Yeah, he does. And no wonderâ€”HE's\ncoming to make his inspections, after all.)
The soldiers seem to be fulfilling their\nduties.
Sir, the town's defenses are impenetrable!\nYou can entrust everything to us, General!

Indeed. Exercise the utmost caution.
Let not so much as a single ant through.
Should anyone be foolish enough to try,
mete them a swift and final judgment.
